<title type="html"><![CDATA[4/3(Sun.)Why You Should Be Wary About Incredible Online Shopping Deals/Why do young people jobless after graduated?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=604&amp;p=627#p627"><![CDATA[
4/3(Sun.) Why You Should Be Wary About Incredible Online Shopping Deals / Why do young people jobless after graduated? The education system needs to be changed. (Host: Ellen)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:35 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:35-9:00 pm Debate<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />--------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session I : Why You Should Be Wary About Incredible Online Shopping Deals<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/167860">https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/167860</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.Have you ever purchased things via websites? What websites do you usually shop (such like momo, shopee, pchome…)?<br />2.When you purchase things from websites, do you use the search engine (suck like feebee, findprice, 比價網) to find the cheapest one first? Or how do you usual search the thing which you want to buy on the website? Please share your experience. <br />3.The article mentioned “When we find something we really want, our judgment is impaired. That's no accident”. Do you agree with it? Why or why not? Any experience to share with?<br />4.Have you ever been scammed from the website purchasing? What did you react or deal with the scam? <br />5.Expect online scam, there are often phone scams. Did you have the experience with phone scams? How did you deal with it?<br />6.Any tip to prevent scams from websites or phones?<br /><br />-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 2: Why do young people jobless after graduated? The education system needs to be changed.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vF36zoA1JcQ">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vF36zoA1JcQ</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.Do you agree with the speaker’s (Matthew McConaughey) points of views? Why or why not?<br />2.Do you think what are the reasons that young people jobless after graduated? <br />3.How do you think of the differences between the education system in your generation and nowadays? (Better, worse, the same)<br />4.How to balance the academic and practical learning from our education? Do you think there is a big gap between what we learn at school and what the company/society requires? <br />5.Any suggestion to shorten the gap between school and company/society? (such like collaboration between industry and school, provide more internships, help students get more understand about their interests/the job what they work in the future….)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=46353">Ellen Lu</a> — Wed Mar 30, 2022 9:34 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
